text.tspan: The Whos, Whats, and Whys of Data Breaches
Every day, almost 4.5 million data records are lost or stolen around the world.
North America is hit especially hard.
As the amount of data in the world increases, the total number of records breached fluctuates, with
a noticeably fewer number of large outlier cases.
Malicious Outsiders are by far the main offenders. The state sponsored and accidental loss categories
are second and third but are nowhere near the magnitude of the malicious outsider category.
